SIMPLE: wrongous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wrongous
<hw>Wron"gous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OE.
<ets>wrongwis</ets>. See <er>Wrong</er>, and cf.
<er>Righteous</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Constituting, or of the nature of, a wrong; unjust;
wrongful.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>Not right; illegal; <as>as,
<ex>wrongous</ex> imprisonment</as>.</def> <rj><au>Craig.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrong-timed</ent>⟦br⟧
